The US embassy in India has said that its official X (formerly Twitter ) account will not be updated regularly due to lapse in appropriations in the US. In a post shared on X, the embassy stated that the pause in regular updates is linked to funding issues that have affected government operations. However, the account will continue to share urgent and security-related information until full operations resume. “Because of the lapse in appropriations, this X account will not be updated regularly until full operations resume, with the exception of urgent safety and security information,” reads the US Embassy in India’s post.The US government entered a partial shut down earlier this week after a standoff in Congress over new restrictions on federal agents involved in Donald Trump’s mass deportation campaign.Funding for several US government departments lapsed after Democratic senators refused to vote for a bill authorizing continued spending by the Department of Homeland Security (DHS).This comes after the US Immigration and Customs Enforcement (ICE) agents killed Alex Pretti in Minnesota’s largest city last week, and Renee Good earlier in January. Senate Democratic Minority Whip Dick Durbin criticised the administration's priorities, saying, "Instead of going after drug smugglers, child predators, and human traffickers, the Trump Administration is wasting valuable resources targeting peaceful protestors in Chicago and Minneapolis." He added, "This Administration continues to make Americans less safe."Russell Vought, the director of the office of management and budget (OMB) shared an official memo on January 30 directing affected agencies to “execute plans for an orderly shutdown”. According to it, appropriations for the following departments expired on January 30
